com.smartsockets
Interface TipcMsgDecryptFuncInterface

public interface TipcMsgDecryptFuncInterface

The user interface for message decryption functions.

This interface can be used to implement any decryption algorithm required by the application. If the applcation registers the implemented interface object by calling TipcMt.setDecryptFunc(com.smartsockets.TipcMsgDecryptFuncInterface, java.lang.Object), then during the message decryption the object's decrypt_func will be called to decrypt the message. A symmetric encryption function should be registered at the publishing client.

See Also:
TipcMt.setDecryptFunc(com.smartsockets.TipcMsgDecryptFuncInterface, java.lang.Object), TipcMsgEncryptFuncInterface
